import Mathlib

open Set Metric

/-
Let U ‚äÇ ‚ÑÇ be a domain and f : U ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ be holomorphic. Show that f is analytic on U; that is, f has a Taylor series expansion around each point with radius of convergence equal to the distance to the nearest singularity, and the series sums to f.

The following formal statement expresses this in terms of differentiability on an open set and the existence of a formal power series (FormalMultilinearSeries) at each point with radius equal to the distance to the complement of U.
-/

theorem holomorphic_on_implies_analytic {U : Set ‚ÑÇ} (hU : IsOpen U) (f : ‚ÑÇ ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ)
  (h : DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ f U) :
  ‚àÄ z ‚àà U, ‚àÉ p : FormalMultilinearSeries ‚ÑÇ ‚ÑÇ ‚ÑÇ,
    HasFPowerSeriesAt f p z ‚àß p.radius = ENNReal.ofReal (dist z (U·∂ú)) := by sorry

The following formal statement expresses this in terms of differentiability on an open set and the existence of a formal power series (FormalMultilinearSeries) at each point with radius equal to the distance to the complement of U.
-/

theorem holomorphic_on_implies_analytic {U : Set ‚ÑÇ} (hU : IsOpen U) (f : ‚ÑÇ ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ)
